author: Joe Buczek
title: Local cross country teams compete in UP state championships
text:
Local cross country teams compete in UP state championships Posted: 
The Sault Ste. Marie boys cross country team finished second at the MHSAA Division 1 Upper Peninsula state championships on Saturday, finishing behind Negaunee with 85 points. 
Aaron Kinsella paced the Blue Devils with a time of 17:36.2. 
On the girls side, Sault Ste. Marie came home in second, nine points behind champion Marquette. 
Mackenzie Kalchik finished fourth individually with a time of 19:21.6. Teammate Megan Arbic also placed sixth, crossing the line in 19:32.2 and Courtney Arbic finished eighth with a time of 19:45.9. 
St. Ignace posted a fourth-place finish in Division 2, with Callie Kammers finishing in 10th with a time of 22:17.6. 
In Division 3 action, Newberry’s Kindred Griffis placed seventh, finishing in 18:12.6. As a team, Newberry finished in sixth place, while Rudyard came home in ninth. Pickford and Engadine also finished 12th and 13th, respectively. 
On the girls side, Newberry’s Natalie Beaulieu defended her individual state title, finishing with a time of 19:24.5. 
Brimley’s Lauren Halvorsen finished in fifth place, while teammate Hannah Lyons secured an eighth-place finish.
